2) You have a OrderService and while application is up and running application is passes for 2 to 3 seconds.
What would be the problem

OrderService Pause / Freeze (2-3 seconds) —
Root Cause AnalysisA 2-3 second pause in a running application is a classic latency spike problem.

#1 — JVM Garbage Collection (Stop-The-World)
All application threads are paused while GC runs → 2-3s freeze

Indicators:
    GC logs show Stop-The-World pauses
    Heap usage spikes before pause, drops after
    Happens periodically (not on every request)

Fix:
# Switch to G1GC (default Java 9+) or ZGC (Java 15+) for low-latency
-XX:+UseG1GC
-XX:MaxGCPauseMillis=200   # Target max pause

# Or ZGC for sub-millisecond pauses (Java 21 LTS recommended)
-XX:+UseZGC

#2  Database Connection Pool Exhaustion
Request waits for available connection from pool → blocks 2-3s

#3 — Kafka Consumer / Producer Blocking
If OrderService publishes or consumes Kafka events:
Producer metadata refresh, broker rebalance, or
consumer poll blocking thread → 2-3s stall

#4 @Transactional Long-Running / Lock Contention
DB row/table lock held too long → other threads queue up → 2-3s wait

#5 Thread Pool Starvation (Tomcat/Async Executors)
All worker threads busy → new requests queue → visible as pause





